LOS ANGELES, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Four people were injured in a series of explosions Thursday at a metal recycling facility in Southern California, U.S. media reported, citing local officials. The incident was reported at about 9:15 a.m. local time in City of Montclair, about 53 km east of Los Angeles. Emergency responders set up a perimeter in the area as firefighters used firehoses to douse piles of pressurized metal cannisters on the ground at the facility, according to KABC-TV, the West Coast flagship station of the ABC television network. "Everything was just exploding like a freaking war over here," witness Albert Castro was quoted as saying by the news outlet. Two of the victims were transported to a hospital by ambulance, while the two others went to a medical center in civilian vehicles, reported KABC-TV, adding that their conditions and details of their injuries were not immediately known. Some nearby schools were reportedly placed on precautionary lockdowns. The cause of the incident is under investigation.  â– 